node.contents: The SQL command "BEGIN TRANSACTION" (the TRANSACTION keyword is optional) is used to take SQLite out of autocommit mode. Note that the BEGIN command does not acquire any locks on the database. After a BEGIN command, a SHARED lock will be acquired when the first SELECT statement is executed. A RESERVED lock will be acquired when the first INSERT, UPDATE, or DELETE statement is executed. No EXCLUSIVE lock is acquired until either the memory cache fills up and must be spilled to disk or until the transaction commits. In this way, the system delays blocking read access to the file file until the last possible moment.
